‘lead teacher’ or financial education champion who coordinates </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">learning</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> across the curriculum and year groups contributes to whole-school high-quality leadership and teaching. This is particularly important for financial education which from September 2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">014 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">will be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> statutory in mathematics and secondary citizenship for the first time, and schools should designate a coordinator to make links, particularly between maths and citizenship, and with PSHE education and other subjects</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and aspects of learning such</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> as careers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 38.25pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 34.42pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">On the point in HMCI’s report that accountability has played a crucial part in the improved success of England’s schools,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">pfeg</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> welcomes the new </span><a href="http://www.democraticlife.org.uk/2013/10/15/minister-david-laws-announces-new-gcse-best-8-performance-measure-which-includes-gcse-citizenship-studies/"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘best 8</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt